 CHOMP v. To lose; to chew on something of which more was bitten off than one
can. Probably related to gnashing of teeth. see BAGBITER. A hand gesture
commonly accom- panies this, consisting of the four fingers held together as
if in a mitten or hand puppet, and the fingers and thumb open and close
rapidly to illustrate a biting action. The gesture alone means CHOMP CHOMP
(see Verb Doubling).